[
    {
        "content": "<p>If you ask a (certain type of) algebraic geometer what a <em>monad</em> is, they will give you the following definition:</p>\n<p>A monad <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">M</span></span></span></span> on a projective variety <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> is a short sequence of coherent sheaves <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">G</mi><mo>→</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">H</mi><mo>→</mo><mn mathvariant=\"script\">0</mn></mrow></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">0\\to\\cal{F}\\to\\cal{G}\\to\\cal{H}\\to0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7805em;vertical-align:-0.0972em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09931em;\">F</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0593em;\">G</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00965em;\">H</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> on <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> that is exact at <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\cal{F}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09931em;\">F</span></span></span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\cal{H}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00965em;\">H</span></span></span></span></span></span> (i.e. such that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\cal{F}\\to\\cal{G}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7805em;vertical-align:-0.0972em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09931em;\">F</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0593em;\">G</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is injective, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">G</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\cal{G}\\to\\cal{H}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7805em;vertical-align:-0.0972em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0593em;\">G</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00965em;\">H</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is surjective, and the composite is zero).</p>\n<p>Is there any way in which this is an example of a monad in the sense of category theory? Or is this just a really terrible unfortunate clash of terminology?</p>",
        "id": 275507813,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Hosgood",
        "timestamp": 1647436210
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is the composite <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">G</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal F \\to \\mathcal G \\to \\mathcal H</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09931em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7805em;vertical-align:-0.0972em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0593em;\">G</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00965em;\">H</span></span></span></span> zero? Wouldn't that be exactness at <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathcal G</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7805em;vertical-align:-0.0972em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0593em;\">G</span></span></span></span>? Maybe I'm just confused.</p>",
        "id": 275508609,
        "sender_full_name": "Joe Moeller",
        "timestamp": 1647436634
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>exactness at <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\cal{G}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7805em;vertical-align:-0.0972em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0593em;\">G</span></span></span></span></span></span> would say that the kernel of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">G</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\cal{G}\\to\\cal{H}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7805em;vertical-align:-0.0972em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0593em;\">G</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.00965em;\">H</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is exactly the image of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">F</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\cal{F}\\to\\cal{G}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7805em;vertical-align:-0.0972em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.09931em;\">F</span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0593em;\">G</span></span></span></span></span></span></span> (i.e. that the cohomology is zero), but here we're just asking for the kernel to be contained inside (and not necessarily equal to) the image</p>",
        "id": 275508883,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Hosgood",
        "timestamp": 1647436800
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What area of algebraic geometry is this term/notion used in?</p>",
        "id": 275509093,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1647436921
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>a lot of projective geometry, e.g. <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1801.00151\">https://arxiv.org/abs/1801.00151</a></p>",
        "id": 275509281,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Hosgood",
        "timestamp": 1647437015
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A quick search suggests that the term goes back to <a href=\"https://londmathsoc.onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1112/plms/s3-14.4.689\">Horrocks: Vector Bundles on the Punctured Spectrum of a Local Ring</a>, where it is introduced at the bottom of p.698. It seems that no explanation for the term is given, but maybe it's motivated by the usage of \"monad\" as <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/infinitesimal%20neighborhood\">meaning infinitesimal neighbourhood</a>?</p>",
        "id": 275514841,
        "sender_full_name": "Tobias Fritz",
        "timestamp": 1647439586
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ah, that's an unfortunate (and disappointing) coincidence then</p>",
        "id": 275516848,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Hosgood",
        "timestamp": 1647440416
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i was hoping to have my mind blown learning how this notion of monad was secretly a monad...</p>",
        "id": 275516886,
        "sender_full_name": "Tim Hosgood",
        "timestamp": 1647440433
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Who knows, maybe there nevertheless is an amazing coincidence about monads being monads? As with what happened with 'spectrum\": the fact that optical spectra are spectra of operators is a mind-blowing coincidence, especially given that both terms were introduced before this connection was known! (Although the mathematical term <a href=\"https://mathoverflow.net/a/9126/27013\">may have been inspired</a> by the physics parlance.)</p>",
        "id": 275518323,
        "sender_full_name": "Tobias Fritz",
        "timestamp": 1647441004
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I wonder who came up with this usage of \"monad\" and when.  That might be a clue.  Meanwhile I'll try to think about how to get an actual monad from this things.</p>",
        "id": 275554591,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1647454162
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monad_(nonstandard_analysis)\">monad</a>, but to answer the question, I think it might have been Leibniz.</p>",
        "id": 275654587,
        "sender_full_name": "Todd Trimble",
        "timestamp": 1647524909
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Leibniz's notion of Monad is much more closely related to Yoneda that the modern notion of Monad.</p>",
        "id": 275713897,
        "sender_full_name": "Jacques Carette",
        "timestamp": 1647545479
    }
]